modules.description: This module defines configuration parameters for an OCurl-based OpenTelemetry backend, including endpoints for traces, metrics, and logs, along with tuning options for batching, threading, and self-tracing. It supports creating and formatting configuration values that control how telemetry data is exported over HTTP. Concrete use cases include setting up export URLs, adjusting batch timeouts, and enabling debug modes for troubleshooting telemetry pipelines.

This module manages HTTP headers and configures an OpenTelemetry backend using OCurl for exporting telemetry data over HTTP. It provides functions to set up global headers, create a backend with specific configuration, and run code within a configured environment. Concrete use cases include configuring trace and metric export endpoints, setting batch timeouts, and enabling debug modes for telemetry pipelines.
